parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the factory-provided jack can cause serious injury, including broken bones, and damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: The jack collapses while in use
causing the vehicle to fall off the jack
resulting in injury to the person working underneath the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transfer case can cause the vehicle to stop abruptly while driving, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly stops or loses power while driving
the transfer case freezes up
the vehicle is unable to move
the vehicle experiences sudden loss of traction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, slip, or hesitate, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates
the vehicle loses power
the vehicle experiences sudden jerking or hesitation
the transmission makes unusual noises
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the coolant system can cause engine overheating, leading to engine damage, breakdowns, and potentially even engine failure, which can result in costly repairs, accidents, or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle overheats
the coolant level drops
the coolant leaks
the temperature gauge is in the red zone
the vehicle stalls or shuts down
the engine makes unusual noises or smells.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty fuel pump can cause the vehicle to stall, particularly in traffic, which can increase the risk of accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or dies while driving
especially in heavy traffic or when accelerating
the engine sputters or hesitates before stalling
the fuel pump makes a loud whining or grinding noise
the vehicle has difficulty starting or has a long crank time.
